and confirm your decision.
Exercising Your Rights through Authorized Agents
Per the CCPA, consumers may exercise their rights through an authorized agent. Therefore,
we have prepared the following guidelines for authorized agents acting on behalf of consumers regarding exercise of consumer’s rights under the CCPA.
If you have a Tuya account
Authorized agents acting on behalf of consumers with a Tuya account can exercise their rights through Tuya account. Please kindly note the following rights will be handled respectively:
1. Right to know: You can check the categories of personal information being collected, processed, shared or used are recorded in this Notice.
2. Right to access and right to be forgotten: You may access to or delete consumer’s personal information through submitting the request in the
Help Center
with technical support.
It is important to note that a valid login is required to access or delete personal information associated with a Tuya account. This safeguard is in place to protect the security of consumer data. Once the request is submitted by the authorized agent, the request will be handled automatically.
If you do not have a Tuya account
If the consumer does not have a Tuya account or would like to export or delete personal information not linked to a Tuya account, the following instructions may allow you to excise your right:
1. Right to know: You can check the categories of personal information being collected, processed, shared or used are recorded in this Notice.
2. Right to access and right to be forgotten: Your personal information will be deleted right after you clean your cookies upon the visiting pages. Or, you can make a request directly to
privacy@tuya.com
. As this request is for data outside of a logged-in Tuya account, we require at least two identification elements, such as a verified email or phone number, for verification purposes prior to processing the request.
